Ultrasound-Based Renal Parenchymal Area and Kidney Function Decline in Infants With Congenital Anomalies of the Kidney and Urinary Tract. 
Lower RPA z-scores were correlated weakly with a higher annual decrease in eGFR (Spearman correlation, 0.35; 95% confidence interval, -0.25 to 0.76). This pilot study shows the feasibility of obtaining RPA from a routine ultrasound and suggests that a lower baseline RPA may be associated with a greater decrease in eGFR over time. Further studies with larger patient cohorts are needed to confirm this association.
